    "id": "safe_sexual_practices",
    "title": "Safe Sexual Practices",
    "category": "Sexual Health",
    "readTime": "9 min read",
    "summary": "Learn how to protect yourself and your partner through communication, consent, protection methods, and regular sexual health care.",
    "content": "# Safe Sexual Practices\n\nSexual health is an important part of overall wellbeing. Safe sexual practices help reduce the risk of sexually transmitted infections (STIs), unintended pregnancies, and unhealthy relationship experiences.\n\n## What Does Safe Sex Mean?\n\nSafe sex refers to behaviors that help protect physical, emotional, and reproductive health during sexual activity.\n\nSafe sex includes:\n\n• Mutual consent\n• Open communication\n• STI prevention\n• Pregnancy prevention when desired\n• Respect for boundaries\n\n## Understanding Consent\n\nConsent means that all people involved freely agree to participate.\n\nConsent should be:\n\n• Clear\n• Voluntary\n• Ongoing\n• Informed\n• Respectful\n\nAnyone can change their mind at any time.\n\n## Protection Methods\n\nDifferent protection methods serve different purposes.\n\n### Condoms\n\nCondoms help reduce the risk of both pregnancy and many sexually transmitted infections.\n\n### Birth Control Methods\n\nExamples include:\n\n• Birth control pills\n• Hormonal implants\n• Hormonal injections\n• Intrauterine devices (IUDs)\n\nThese methods help prevent pregnancy but do not protect against most STIs.\n\n## STI Prevention\n\nReducing STI risk may involve:\n\n• Condom use\n• Regular testing\n• Honest communication with partners\n• Limiting exposure to high-risk situations\n\n## Importance Of Testing\n\nMany STIs may not cause noticeable symptoms.\n\nRegular testing helps identify infections early and allows timely treatment.\n\n## Communication Matters\n\nHealthy communication includes discussing:\n\n• Boundaries\n• Expectations\n• Protection preferences\n• Sexual health history\n\nThese conversations help build trust and respect.\n\n## Emotional Wellbeing\n\nSexual wellbeing involves more than physical health.\n\nHealthy relationships should involve:\n\n• Respect\n• Trust\n• Communication\n• Emotional safety\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: If someone looks healthy, they cannot have an STI.\n\nFact: Many STIs cause no obvious symptoms and can only be detected through testing.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nSafe sexual practices involve consent, communication, appropriate protection, STI awareness, and respect for personal boundaries. These habits support both physical and emotional wellbeing."
