    "id": "thyroid_and_periods",
    "title": "Thyroid & Your Menstrual Cycle",
    "category": "Women's Health",
    "readTime": "8 min read",
    "summary": "Discover how thyroid hormones influence periods, fertility, energy levels, and overall reproductive health.",
    "content": "# Thyroid & Your Menstrual Cycle\n\nThe thyroid is a small butterfly-shaped gland located in the neck.\n\nAlthough small, it plays a major role in regulating metabolism, energy levels, body temperature, and reproductive health.\n\nWhen thyroid hormones become imbalanced, menstrual cycles can also be affected.\n\n## What Does The Thyroid Do?\n\nThe thyroid produces hormones that help control how the body uses energy.\n\nThese hormones influence many organs, including the reproductive system.\n\n## Hypothyroidism\n\nHypothyroidism occurs when the thyroid produces too little hormone.\n\nCommon symptoms include:\n\n• Fatigue\n• Weight gain\n• Feeling cold\n• Dry skin\n• Depression\n• Heavy periods\n• Irregular cycles\n\n## Hyperthyroidism\n\nHyperthyroidism occurs when the thyroid produces too much hormone.\n\nCommon symptoms include:\n\n• Weight loss\n• Anxiety\n• Rapid heartbeat\n• Difficulty sleeping\n• Light or absent periods\n• Increased sweating\n\n## Effects On Menstrual Health\n\nThyroid disorders may cause:\n\n• Missed periods\n• Heavy bleeding\n• Light bleeding\n• Irregular cycles\n• Fertility challenges\n\n## Effects On Fertility\n\nBecause thyroid hormones help regulate ovulation, untreated thyroid conditions may make conception more difficult.\n\nProper treatment often improves reproductive health.\n\n## When To Seek Medical Advice\n\nTalk to a healthcare professional if you experience:\n\n• Sudden cycle changes\n• Persistent fatigue\n• Unexplained weight changes\n• Difficulty becoming pregnant\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: Thyroid problems only affect metabolism.\n\nFact: Thyroid hormones influence many body systems, including menstrual and reproductive health.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nThe thyroid plays a key role in menstrual health, fertility, metabolism, and energy. Thyroid disorders can affect cycle regularity but are often manageable with proper medical care."
  },
