    "id": "period_nutrition_guide",
    "title": "Nutrition During Your Period",
    "category": "Nutrition",
    "readTime": "8 min read",
    "summary": "Learn which foods may help support energy levels, comfort, and overall wellbeing during menstruation.",
    "content": "# Nutrition During Your Period\n\nMenstruation places unique demands on the body. Some people experience fatigue, cramps, headaches, bloating, and food cravings during their period.\n\nA balanced diet cannot eliminate every symptom, but it can help support energy levels and overall wellbeing.\n\n## Why Nutrition Matters During Menstruation\n\nDuring menstruation, the body loses blood and undergoes hormonal changes.\n\nNutrition helps support:\n\n• Energy production\n• Iron levels\n• Hydration\n• Muscle function\n• Overall health\n\n## Iron-Rich Foods\n\nIron helps transport oxygen throughout the body.\n\nPeople who experience menstrual bleeding may benefit from including iron-rich foods in their diet.\n\nExamples include:\n\n• Lentils\n• Beans\n• Spinach\n• Lean meats\n• Tofu\n• Fortified cereals\n\nPairing iron-rich foods with vitamin C sources may help improve iron absorption.\n\n## Magnesium-Rich Foods\n\nMagnesium supports muscle and nerve function.\n\nFoods containing magnesium include:\n\n• Pumpkin seeds\n• Almonds\n• Cashews\n• Dark leafy greens\n• Whole grains\n\n## Hydration\n\nDrinking enough water may help support normal body functions and overall comfort.\n\nHydration is important throughout the menstrual cycle.\n\n## Protein For Energy\n\nProtein helps support stable energy levels.\n\nGood sources include:\n\n• Eggs\n• Fish\n• Chicken\n• Greek yogurt\n• Lentils\n• Chickpeas\n\n## Managing Food Cravings\n\nFood cravings are common before and during periods.\n\nInstead of strict restriction, focus on balance:\n\n• Fruits\n• Nuts\n• Whole grains\n• Yogurt\n• Dark chocolate in moderation\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: You should avoid all exercise and focus only on eating comfort foods during your period.\n\nFact: Balanced nutrition, hydration, and appropriate physical activity can support overall wellbeing.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nIron-rich foods, protein, hydration, fruits, vegetables, and whole grains can help support energy levels and overall health during menstruation."
  },
