    "readTime": "9 min read",
    "summary": "Discover how healthy eating habits support reproductive health and fertility for those trying to conceive.",
    "content": "# Nutrition For Fertility\n\nFertility is influenced by many factors, including age, genetics, lifestyle, and overall health.\n\nNutrition is one important piece of the fertility picture.\n\n## Why Nutrition Matters\n\nThe body needs adequate nutrients to support:\n\n• Hormone production\n• Ovulation\n• Egg health\n• Reproductive function\n• Overall wellbeing\n\n## Important Nutrients\n\n### Folate\n\nFolate supports cell growth and development.\n\nSources include:\n\n• Leafy greens\n• Lentils\n• Beans\n• Citrus fruits\n\n### Protein\n\nProtein supports hormone production and tissue health.\n\nExamples:\n\n• Eggs\n• Fish\n• Poultry\n• Lentils\n• Tofu\n\n### Healthy Fats\n\nHealthy fats play a role in hormone production.\n\nSources include:\n\n• Avocados\n• Olive oil\n• Nuts\n• Seeds\n• Fatty fish\n\n### Iron\n\nIron supports oxygen transport and overall health.\n\nSources include:\n\n• Spinach\n• Beans\n• Lentils\n• Lean meats\n\n## Maintaining A Healthy Lifestyle\n\nHealthy eating works best when combined with:\n\n• Adequate sleep\n• Physical activity\n• Stress management\n• Medical care when needed\n\n## Foods To Enjoy More Often\n\n• Fruits\n• Vegetables\n• Whole grains\n• Lean proteins\n• Healthy fats\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: A single fertility food can dramatically increase your chances of pregnancy.\n\nFact: Fertility is influenced by many factors. Long-term healthy habits are more important than any single food.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nA balanced diet rich in protein, healthy fats, fruits, vegetables, and essential nutrients supports overall reproductive health and fertility."
  },
