    "id": "ovulation_symptoms",
    "title": "Ovulation Symptoms",
    "category": "Fertility",
    "readTime": "7 min read",
    "summary": "Learn the common physical and emotional signs that may occur around ovulation.",
    "content": "# Ovulation Symptoms ✨\n\nOvulation is the process where a mature egg is released from an ovary.\n\nFor many people, ovulation occurs once during each menstrual cycle.\n\nSome individuals notice clear signs that ovulation is approaching, while others experience few or no symptoms.\n\n## What Happens During Ovulation?\n\nA surge in luteinizing hormone (LH) triggers the release of an egg.\n\nThe egg then travels into the fallopian tube where fertilization may occur.\n\n## Common Ovulation Symptoms\n\n### Increased Cervical Mucus\n\nOne of the most reliable signs.\n\nCervical mucus often becomes:\n\n• Clear\n• Slippery\n• Stretchy\n• Similar to raw egg whites\n\n### Mild Pelvic Pain (Mittelschmerz)\n\nSome people feel:\n\n• A mild ache\n• A brief cramp\n• Pressure on one side of the lower abdomen\n\n### Increased Libido\n\nMany individuals report increased sexual desire around ovulation.\n\nThis is believed to be influenced by hormonal changes.\n\n### Breast Tenderness\n\nHormonal shifts may cause temporary breast sensitivity.\n\n### Increased Energy\n\nMany women describe feeling:\n\n• More energetic\n• More social\n• More motivated\n\n### Heightened Sense Of Smell\n\nSome research suggests sensory awareness may temporarily increase during ovulation.\n\n## Ovulation Symptoms Are Different For Everyone\n\nSome people experience several symptoms.\n\nOthers experience none at all.\n\nLack of noticeable symptoms does not necessarily mean ovulation is not occurring.\n\n## When To Talk To A Healthcare Professional\n\nSeek medical advice if:\n\n• Periods are highly irregular\n• Ovulation is difficult to identify\n• You suspect hormonal imbalances\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: You can always feel ovulation.\n\nFact: Many people ovulate without experiencing noticeable symptoms.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nOvulation symptoms may include clear cervical mucus, mild pelvic discomfort, increased libido, breast tenderness, and higher energy levels. Every body experiences ovulation differently."
  },
