    "summary": "Know the signs and symptoms that may indicate it's time to consult a gynecologist for expert care.",
    "content": "# When To See A Gynecologist 👩‍⚕️\n\nMany women wonder whether their symptoms are 'normal' or whether they should seek professional medical advice.\n\nA gynecologist specializes in reproductive and sexual health and can help diagnose, treat, and manage many conditions.\n\n## Routine Visits Matter\n\nEven if you feel healthy, regular gynecological checkups can help support long-term reproductive health.\n\n## Reasons To Schedule A Visit\n\n### Severe Period Pain\n\nIf cramps:\n\n• Prevent normal activities\n• Require frequent pain medication\n• Continue worsening\n\nA medical evaluation is recommended.\n\n### Very Heavy Bleeding\n\nSeek medical advice if:\n\n• You soak through pads frequently\n• Pass large blood clots\n• Feel dizzy or weak\n\n### Irregular Periods\n\nPeriods that are consistently irregular may indicate hormonal imbalances.\n\n### Missed Periods\n\nEspecially if pregnancy is unlikely.\n\n### Pelvic Pain\n\nPersistent pelvic pain should always be evaluated.\n\n### Unusual Vaginal Discharge\n\nSeek medical attention if discharge has:\n\n• Strong odor\n• Unusual color\n• Accompanying itching or irritation\n\n### Pain During Intercourse\n\nPain is not something you should simply tolerate.\n\nA gynecologist can help identify potential causes.\n\n### Fertility Concerns\n\nConsider evaluation if:\n\n• Under 35 and trying for 12 months\n• 35 or older and trying for 6 months\n\n### Symptoms Of PCOS, Endometriosis, Or Fibroids\n\nExamples include:\n\n• Excessive period pain\n• Heavy bleeding\n• Irregular cycles\n• Chronic pelvic discomfort\n\n## Questions You Can Ask\n\nA gynecologist can help with:\n\n• Birth control options\n• Menstrual concerns\n• Fertility questions\n• Pregnancy planning\n• Menopause symptoms\n• Sexual health concerns\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: You only need a gynecologist if something is wrong.\n\nFact: Preventive care and regular checkups are important even when you feel healthy.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nYou should consider seeing a gynecologist for severe period pain, heavy bleeding, irregular cycles, pelvic pain, fertility concerns, or any symptom affecting your quality of life. Early evaluation often leads to better treatment and peace of mind."
